<p class="H3"><b>Do you have a question?&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></p>

<p class="s" style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>1) Where can I find information on insurance plans available to associates?</b></p>
<p class="s" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><i>Visit the section entitled Benefits and click through to Insurance Plans.</i></p>

<p class="s" style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>2) Is diversity important to Bank of America?</b></p>
<p class="s" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><i>At Bank of America our goal is to draw on the strength of every individual by promoting a diverse workplace. Learn more by clicking on the section diversity.</i></p>

<p class="s" style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>3) What are the lines of businesses that an employee could work within?</b></p>
<p class="s" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><i>Bank of America is comprised of seven lines of business which are all essential to the bank's overall financial success.  You can learn more each of the lines of business by accessing Corporate Information.</i></p>

<p class="s" style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>4) Are there flexible work arrangements available?</b></p>
<p class="s" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><i>Our associates enjoy options such as flex-time, compressed workweeks, telecommuting, select time and phase-in. To read more on these options click 	through to Benefits and Work/Life Balance.</i></p>

<p class="s" style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>5) What is the process as a new employee to coming onboard?</b></p>
<p class="s" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><i>New associates are given full support when coming on board with Bank of America.  To learn more about the process visit Our Staffing Process section.</i></p>

<p class="s" style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>6) Where could I read more on the financial success of Bank of America?</b></p>
<p class="s" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><i>To understand more of where Bank of America has been and where the company 	is continuing to grow click through to corporate information and the link for Annual Report.</i></p>

<p class="s" style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>7) Is there a sense of team while working at Bank of America?</b></p>
<p class="s" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><i>Team Bank of America is a worldwide organization where associates and retirees can work together in community volunteering programs. Learn more by clicking through to Corporate Information and Community.</i></p>

<p class="s" style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>8) Does Bank of America have a policy on hiring relatives of current associates?</b></p>
<p class="s" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><i>We do not have a written policy concerning hiring family members, relatives and close friends of current employees or the Corporate Board of Directors. We review each situation on an individual basis.</i></p>
